    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Removal - Case-to-Head Tubes</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.3.11" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Case-to-Head Tubes</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, wear safety glasses with side shields whenever
                    using compressed air for cleaning purposes. Limit the air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi). See
                    <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, it is recommended that the case-to-head tubes be replaced each time they
                    are removed. The D-rings are not replaceable. If you reuse the case-to-head tubes, you assume the
                    risk for leakage. You must inspect each D-ring carefully for evidence of cutting, abrasion or
                    twisting and never reuse a tube exhibiting any of these seal conditions.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The procedure for removing the case-to-head tube assembly is the same for either side of the
                    engine.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">In the event the case-to-head tube was removed with the case-to-head plug prior to
                high-pressure rail removal, the following step will be uneccessary. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="e300517">case-to-head tube assembly</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the case-to-head tube, push the Case-To-Head Tube Removal Tool into tube and
                tighten T-handle until a positive lock can be felt. Pull out tube and discard. See
                <hotlnk xrefid="e30005C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
